    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>::Clack::.

The top of the cube folds away, revealing the gift within - a ring, loosed from its cradle. Perhaps it got loose on its own. Or perhaps the daughter solved the puzzle long ago... and rejected the gift. 

You lift the ring from its cradle, tuck it away, and snap the cube closed. 

{LOOT: Should be a small item a father would give his daughter who he's fought alongside in battle. Shouldn't be something that would actually harm her. May be a ring (and I've included that above for now).}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>The box is now empty. All that remains are the messages from a father to his daughter. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
